Vice President Kamala Harris spoke at the Lake Mead Overlook in Boulder City, Nevada, addressing the issue of water scarcity and the impact of the climate crisis. She emphasized the importance of water for all living beings and the need to address the current drought conditions. Harris highlighted the Build Back Better Agenda, which focuses on climate, families, jobs, and health. She mentioned the Bipartisan Infrastructure Deal and the Build Back Better Agenda as solutions to invest in water infrastructure, water recycling, desalination, and drought contingency plans. The Vice President also emphasized the creation of good union jobs in fields like plumbing, electricians, and pipefitters. Additionally, she emphasized the need to combat the climate crisis through investments in clean energy and electric vehicles to reduce emissions. Harris called for a sense of urgency and responsibility to pass these bills to protect the environment and ensure the well-being of future generations.